Police have opened a missing person inquiry following the disappearance of Siphosethu Dakuse, 20, who left  home for school on May 13 and never returned. Police spokesperson Captain Mluleki Mbi said information was later received that she attended a party in Braelyn, East London, over the past weekend. Anyone who can assist the police in their investigation is requested to contact the investigating officer, Detective Sergeant Lizo Mancam, on 084-810-9002 or Crime Stop on 08600-10111. All information will be treated with confidentiality. HeraldLIVE